Letter of Thanks and Gift to Kim Jong Il from Chinese Ambassador to DPRK  
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a letter and gift by Liu Xiaoming, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, expressing thanks to him for the successful torch relay for the 29th Olympic Games held in Pyongyang.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter and gift were conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, by Liu Xiaoming on May 5.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Chinese Ambassador to DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met with Liu Xiaoming, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, and had a friendly talk with him at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on May 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing thanks to the party, government and people of the DPRK for rendering sincere help in the torch relay for the 29th Olympic Games held in Pyongyang, Liu Xiaoming noted that this event marked an occasion in boosting the friendly relations between the peoples of China and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is the steadfast policy of the party and government of China to steadily consolidate and develop the Sino-DPRK friendly ties, he stressed that China would make positive efforts to boost the friendship with the DPRK in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Thae Jong, vice department director of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, and staff members of the Chinese embassy here.

Nepalese Organization Decides to Confer Peace Prize on Kim Jong Il  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The Nepal Journalist Association decided to award the "Nepalese International Peace Prize" to General Secretary Kim Jong Il on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A decision was adopted at the 18th general meeting of the association held from April 29 to 30.

10th Pyongyang Seminar on Medical Science Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The 10th Pyongyang seminar on medical science of Koreans at home and abroad was held at the People's Palace of Culture on May 5 and 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by officials in the field of public health including Ri Pong Hun, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Medical Association, and medical scientists and members of the delegation of Korean scientists in the United States led by Pak Mun Jae and Ri Jong Su, secretary general of the Germany-Korea Medicine Association.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Pong Hun in his opening address expressed belief that medical scientists at home and abroad would positively contribute to the development of the medical science and technology of the Korean nation to a higher stage with desire to contribute to the prosperity of the country and improvement of the people's health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched video on which seminars held in the last period were recorded. Then followed a general lecture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar was divided into panels of the internal and external medicines. Presented there were tens of papers introducing valuable research achievements that gave answers to theoretical and practical issues arising in developing the medical science and experience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing address was made and souvenirs and certificates were conferred on speakers who presented excellent papers.

Computer Multimedia Literary Library Brought out 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Kim Il Sung University has recently brought out a computer multimedia literary library named "Mirae" (version 2.0). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It contains more than a million pages of books along with 350,000 lemmas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of its letters amounts to 300,000,000. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the data are famous art pieces created by the three generals of Mt. Paektu and their works, aphorisms of General Secretary Kim Jong Il and books and materials for studying the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In addition, it gives more than 10,000 literary works including a series of novels "Immortal History", "Immortal Leadership" and "On the One Road of Loyalty", selection of Korean classical literature, selection of Korean modern literature, selection of Korean short novels, selection of world literature and  selection of world children's literature, which have been published in the DPRK. It also reflects the "Grand Dictionary of Literature", "Grand Korean Dictionary ", history of literature and literary theory and various kinds of common knowledge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Mirae" (version 2.0) is being widely disseminated through CD and homepage.

KCNA on Lee Myung Bak's "Diplomacy of Value Concepts" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- It is the poor political servant who lives in others' senses and dances to the tune of others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Typical of such disgraceful servants is Lee Myung Bak of south Korea. During his junkets to the U.S. and Japan, he called for alliance with foreign forces and confrontation with the fellow countrymen, imitating others' "diplomacy of value concepts." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He prattled that south Korea and the U.S. should build the "alliance of confidence" in order to expand co-interests in military affairs, political diplomacy, economy, social culture and all other fields on the basis of the common concepts of value called "democracy" and "market economy." And he went the lengths of claiming that "the most important task facing south Korea and the U.S. is how to cope with north Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that "principled pragmatism" advocated by the Lee Myung Bak gentries as "doctrine of diplomacy" is, in fact, a treacherous and sycophantic "doctrine" as it is a mixture of "pragmatism" and "diplomacy of value concepts" from the U.S. and Japan and the doctrine of anti-DPRK confrontation from the "Yusin" architects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee Myung Bak regime has been steeped in flunkeyism and treachery to the marrow of its bones from its outset. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If not, how could he do such foolish things as peddling in the U.S. the "proposal" on the relations with the fellow countrymen, which includes the issue of establishing the "liaison office" for "diplomacy towards the north" like relationship between countries? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is to be done between the fellow countrymen is not diplomacy but to achieve unity and peace and prosperity under the banner of "By our nation itself." So it is nonsense to talk about diplomatic relationship between the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Flunkeyism makes a man become an idiot and if a nation follows it, it will destroy its own country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As it is mad with flunkeyism, the Lee Myung Bak group has turned to be a fool totally ignorant of the inter-Korean relations and a political servant of the outsiders who poses threat to the lives of the fellow countrymen by subserviently opening the beef market and resisting the reduction of aggression forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "pragmatic diplomacy" of the Lee Myung Bak regime is just "tribute-offering diplomacy," "diplomacy of drain on resources for outsiders" and "treacherous diplomacy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is the results of the first overseas trip of traitor Lee who has pursued the "tightened alliance," talking about the "commonness in concepts of value." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee Myung Bak should be mindful that the developments in recent years, in which pro-American elements were expelled from power in Europe and Japan one after another, are a serious warning to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Time will prove how contradictory and catastrophic the Lee Myung Bak group's mixture of "pragmatism" and the anti-DPRK, sycophantic and treacherous "diplomacy of value concepts" is.

Lee Myung Bak's Junkets to U.S. and Japan Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- During his visits to the U.S. and the Japanese masters traitor Lee Myung Bak did nothing but selling off the dignity of the nation and the interests of the south Koreans and inciting anachronistic confrontation with the DPRK, says Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What he uttered during his recent junkets to the U.S. and Japan were sinister anti-reunification outbursts aimed to do harm to the fellow countrymen in cooperation with the outsiders, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not content with talking about "threat" and "nuclear abandonment," Lee went the lengths of inciting anti-DPRK war moves, asserting that it should never be "tolerated". This glaringly reveals his dirty colors as a guy keen on dependence on outsiders and anti-reunification confrontation as it indicates his inveterate enmity toward the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He cried that he would not negotiate with the DPRK, talking about "blackmail" from it, while defending "no nukes, opening and 3,000 dollars", his anti-reunification policy toward it. This was an open agitation for confrontation with the DPRK. The traitor even said that "not only the south but also the north should be changed", a total denial of the north-south relations that have undergone change after the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. The "change of the south" touted by him reflects his intention to stop national cooperation and "change of the north" his attempt to invade the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The true nature of his junkets for inciting confrontation with the DPRK was brought into bolder relief in the "human rights racket" kicked up by him. The traitor took fault with the non-existent "human rights" issue, a provocation little short of infringing upon the high dignity and authority of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation will certainly reckon the heinous crimes committed by the traitor keen on serving the outsiders and inciting confrontation against the reunification.

U.S. Moves to Bring New Nuclear-powered Carrier to Japan under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is going to permanently keep nuclear-powered carrier George Washington at a Japanese port to replace flattop Kitty Hawk there. George Washington which is to arrive at the Yokosuka Port in August is said to perform operation duties in waters around the Korean Peninsula also in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, papers today say the U.S. intention to have new carrier instead of the old one in waters around the Korean Peninsula on a permanent basis is a serious military move which can never be overlooked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun cites facts to prove that the ultra-modern military hardware is being bolstered up in areas around the peninsula, dismissing it as a deliberate and premeditated move to drive the situation on the peninsula to the brink of a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. warmongers have become all the more pronounced in posing a military threat to the DPRK while shipping huge up-to-date military hardware to areas around the peninsula. This is a vivid expression of their undisguised act of wrecking peace and the hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. advocates "dialogue" in front but behind the scene it escalates military action for attacking the DPRK, straining tension on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. attitude of grinding sword of aggression against the DPRK behind the scene of "dialogue" shows that there is no change in its strategy for aggression against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. warmongers spur the moves to provoke a new Korean war under the signboard of "dialogue" only to push the DPRK to bolstering its war deterrent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should clearly understand the strength and will of the DPRK and give up the attempt to provoke a war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson in a signed commentary denounces the U.S. moves to bring the carrier to Japan, dismissing it as a revelation of sinister plot to invade the DPRK by force and put the Asian region under its military domination with Japan as the most important stronghold.

S. Korean Puppet Air Force to Stage Military Exercises
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The south Korean puppet air force announced that it would stage military exercises for three days, starting on May 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exercises, to be waged by its 17th and 18th combat air divisions, are aimed at increasing the capability for combined operation with different fighter planes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bellicose force declared that it would transfer one wing of F-4s from the 17th combat air division to the 18th combat air division for the exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military exercises fully reveal the bellicose colors of the Lee Myung Bak group.

Suppression of Progressive Movement Forces Assailed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The security authorities of south Korea announced on May 1 that they have defined 25 civic and social organizations and political parties, including the Democratic Labour Party, the Headquarters of the All-People Movement for Checking the south Korea-U.S. FTA and the Federation of Stall Keepers and organizations affiliated to the Solidarity for Progress and the (south) Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, as organizations involved in illegal violence and demonstration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 17 organizations of them are trade unions staging long-term strikes and sit-ins in demand of the repeal of part-time job and the vital rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Police Office and the Ministry of Administration and Security took such action against them, charging that they led "violent demonstrations" last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since traitor Lee Myung Bak came to power, such fascist repressive steps reminding one of the past period of military dictatorship have been taken one after another in south Korea as the use of electric shock apparatus and tear liquid, the organization of team specialized in arrest, the introduction of the system for immediate punishment and the plan for strictly controlling any illegal group action.

Anti-"Government" Rally Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- More than 20,000 members of trade unions of government employees including the Government Employees' Union in south Korea held an anti-"government" rally in Youido, Seoul on May 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the rally speakers denounced the "government" for trying to railroad the "amendment to the law on pension of government employees", which imposes unilateral sacrifice on the employees, through the "National Assembly" against their will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They warned that if the present "government" retrogressively revises the above-said law and conducts restructuring, they will go on a strike. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the government employees are not servants simply working on instruction, they called upon them to struggle in unity.

Struggle against Import of American Beef Unabated in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Struggle of people from different social standings is going on day after day in south Korea against traitor Lee Myung Bak for totally allowing the import of beef from the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A large-scale candlelight rally was held at Chonggye Plaza in Kwanghwamun of Seoul on Saturday night in the wake of similar rally on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by members of political parties and civic and social organizations including the Democratic Labour Party and the Headquarters of the All-People Movement for Checking the S. Korea-U.S. FTA and citizens and students, at least 20,000 all told. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the rally, the Citizens' Solidarity against Policy staged a signature campaign against the import of American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the organization informed the citizens of the danger of "mad cow disease," calling upon them to turn out in the struggle to oppose the import of the American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, an all-people cultural event against the import of American beef was held in front of a bell house in Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar demonstrations and rallies took place in different parts of south Korea including Pusan, Kwangju and Taegu.

Lee Myung Bak Regime's Arms Buildup under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The Lee Myung Bak regime at the Defense Promotion Committee in late April decided to additionally introduce 21 F-15Ks and hundreds of latest air-to-ground cruise missiles to go with them from the U.S. in the period from 2010 to 2012. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is said that it will also purchase fifth generation fighters equipped with Stealth function and technology related to the establishment of Patriot missile defense system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Minju Joson Tuesday observes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a clear proof showing that the Lee Myung Bak regime's sycophancy toward the U.S. and its moves for inciting confrontation with the fellow countrymen have reached their extremes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee Myung Bak group's moves to purchase latest war hardware are a dangerous criminal act aimed to mount a preemptive attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its arms buildup for preemptive attack on the DPRK can never be allowed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If such moves are overlooked the north-south relations will go off track and a new war, a nuclear war may break out on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Huge costs needed for the purchase of the war hardware are to be borne by taxes collected from the south Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee Myung Bak regime is, indeed, a war regime keen on sycophancy toward the U.S. as it fattens U.S. military monopolies through the drain on resources for the U.S. at the cost of the blood and sweat of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Koreans can not but rise against the Lee Myung Bak regime's moves for confrontation with the fellow countrymen in order to live in peaceful environment free from war disasters and not to have their blood sucked any longer.

Anniversaries of Kim Jong Il's Works Marked in Italy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- A meeting took place in Italy on May 1 to mark the 13th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's work "Giving Priority to Ideological Work Is Essential for Accomplishing Socialism" and the 11th anniversary of his work "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the meeting were Kim Jong Il's works and books introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by figures of the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, the Italian Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, the New World Association and a university and other people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Matteo Carbonelli, secretary general of the European society, lauded Kim Jong Il as the great leader who performed undying feats in leading the human cause of independence and the socialist movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism is now actively reviving and advancing worldwide, Matteo Carbonelli, noted, stressing that socialism of the DPRK led by Kim Jong Il would continue to emerge victorious in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Aldo Bernardini, chairman of the Italian committee, noted that the vitality and validity of the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung and developed in depth by Kim Jong Il are being fully displayed in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the struggle of the Korean people for building a great prosperous powerful nation and achieving the national reunification is sure to triumph as they are led by Kim Jong Il and have the Juche idea.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona Unidad No. 1105 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 6 de mayo (ATCC) -- El Dirigente  Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea inspecciono la Unidad No. 1105 del EPC que adquirio el Titulo del Septimo Regimiento de O Jung Hup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Tras hacer conocimiento del estado de cumplimiento del deber de la unidad, el Comandante Supremo vio los ejercicios de mando de estado mayor y de manejo de canones e indico las tareas que se presentan en el mayor fortalecimiento de combatividad de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Senalo que todos los comandantes de la unidad deben organizar todas las labores poniendo en su centro los ejercicios, y el trabajo militar y politico de la unidad debe dirigirse y someterse a hacerlos bien. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Al recorrer la casa cultural de los militares, biblioteca y otras instalaciones culturales y educativas, se entero del estado de la labor politica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Dijo que deben formar a todos los militares como los combatientes de vanguardia de la revolucion armados con la elevada conciencia revolucionaria y clasista y hacer de ellos los heroes juveniles de la epoca del Songun (priorizacion militar) dispuestos a amar fervientemente a la patria y luchar dedicando su juventud y vida por la patria como heroe Ri Su Bok. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Departio cordialmente con Kim Myong Chol laureado con "Premio de Honor Juvenil Kim Il Sung".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Gracias a que el EPC, colectividad de los indoblegables combatientes fuertes en la idea y la conviccion, se desempena como el pilar de la revolucion, el socialismo coreano saldra siempre victorioso, enseno. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Recorrio el Centro de Cultura Fisica para los Soldados, base de servicio publico nuevamente construida en la unidad y otras instalaciones de intendencia prestando gran atencion a la vida de los militares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Se mostro muy satisfecho de que la unidad ofrecio a los militares comodas condiciones de vida y evaluo los esfuerzos del jefe quien al servir durante mas de 30 anos en el mismo puesto hizo muchas cosas y otros oficiales de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Destaco que la unidad laureada con el Titulo del Septimo Regimiento de O Jung Hup es ejemplo en todos los aspectos tanto en los ejercicios militares y politicos como en la labor de abastecimiento, en la cultura y moral, la administracion de la unidad y otros aspectos y evaluo altamente sus exitos logrados en el pasado. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
La realidad de hoy, en que todas las unidades registraron un cambio trascendental en el abastecimiento e hacen un gran aporte al fortalecimiento de la combatividad, prueba practicamente la justicia de las instrucciones del Presidente Kim Il Sung segun las cuales la labor de abastecimiento es justamente la labor politica, asevero el Comandante Supremo y anadio la necesidad de mantener con firmeza este trabajo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Acto seguido, presencio  la funcion artistica de los militares de una compania adscrita a la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Y se fotografio junto con los militares de la unidad y sus familiares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su.

Kim Jong Il recibe "Premio Internacional de la Paz de Nepal"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 6 de mayo (ATCC) -- La Asociacion de Periodistas de Nepal decidio conceder el "Premio Internacional de la Paz de Nepal" al Dirigente Kim Jong Il con motivo del aniversario 60 de la fundacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La resolucion correspondiente fue aprobada en la XVIII asamblea general de la mencionada entidad celebrada los dias 29 y 30 de abril.
